---
const personalImageAlt = "Portrait of Juan Luis Carrasco"
---

<article class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-8 text-gray-300 md:flex-row">
    <div class="[&>p]:mb-4 [&_strong]:text-yellow-100 [&_strong]:font-normal [&_strong]:font-mono text-pretty order-2 md:order-1">
        <p>
            I am <strong>Juan Luis Carrasco Merchán</strong>. From an early age I've been deeply
            interested in technology &mdash; a passion that has shaped both my personal and
            professional journey. I started out writing BASIC as a kid and never really stopped.
        </p>
        <p>
            I have extensive experience in <strong>software development and system architecture</strong>,
            with a strong emphasis on agile methodologies, scalability and clean design. I currently
            work as a Domain Architect, helping replace legacy monoliths with well-bounded services.
        </p>
        <p>
            I'm an active supporter of the open-source community and I'm honoured to be a contributor
            to the official
            <a
                href="https://android-review.googlesource.com/q/owner:jlcarrasco1990%2540gmail.com+status:merged"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="rounded-sm focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring focus-visible:ring-yellow-500/80 focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-gray-950"
            >
                <strong class="hover:text-yellow-500">Android source code</strong></a>.
        </p>
        <p>
            I also co-founded
            <a
                href="https://securekids.es"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="rounded-sm focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring focus-visible:ring-yellow-500/80 focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-gray-950"
            >
                <strong class="hover:text-yellow-500">SecureKids</strong></a>,
            a parental-control application built to help families keep their children safe on the internet.
        </p>
    </div>
    <img
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        width="256"
        height="256"
        src="/me.webp"
        alt={personalImageAlt}
        class="order-1 object-cover w-64 h-64 p-1 md:order-2 rotate-3 lg:p-2 aspect-square rounded-2xl bg-yellow-500/5 ring-1 ring-white/20"
        style="object-position: 50% 50%"
    />
</article>
